result.name: 三一 玫瑰餃

reviews.text: Great food. Reasonable price. A bit packed, please expect to wait a bit during peak hour.

The dumpling size is rather small. Price rather on the high side for the small portions. 

The truffle fries was also soft and disappointing. 

Overall, nothing worth visiting.
A little expensive for dumplings but tastes good.
The pan-fried dumpling with Raclette cheese is very good, I think I have never seen this dish anywhere else in Hong Kong. The staff guy is friendly. Atmosphere and hygiene are ok.
Good food, Cozy place
